cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SE 

The paper deals with data pre-processing, which is a common task in machine learning and data mining. The use of Random Forests to learn the impact of pre-processing operators on the performance of classification algorithms suggests that the paper belongs to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with improving the predictive accuracy of classifiers, which is a common goal in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of pre-processing operators to transform data is also relevant to Database Systems (cs.DB). Finally, the development of a tool to assist non-expert users suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
